HEADWORD: Lithotrity
<hw>Li*thot"ri*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Litho-</ets> + L. <ets>terere</ets>, <ets>tritum</ets>, to
rub, grind.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The operation of breaking a
stone in the bladder or urethrea into small pieces capable of being
voided; lithotripsy.</def>⟦br⟧
